did.unittitle: IBT Central Region Freight Joint Area Committee Transcript Records
did.abstract: This collection consists of typed stenographic notes relating to the Central Confernece of the International Brotherhood of Teamsters. The articles include committee meetings, contract negotiations, grievance hearings, change of operations statuses and discharge cases under the National Master Freight Agreeement. The articles range in date from 1954-2010.
did.materialspec: For many Change of Operation Committee Meeting transcripts, there are sizable gaps in the records.

bioghist.head: Biographical
bioghist.p: This collection was created by the Central Conference of Teamsters. The Conference consisted of Local Unions and State Councils from the Midwestern United States. Many of the documents were created in Chicago, IL. Over time they were housed at Teamster headquarters in Washington, DC. In 2014, they were transferred to The George Washington University where they remain today.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized into one series. It is arranged chronologically.

prefercite.head: Citation
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way:
Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository.

Example: James Oglethorpe to the Trustees, 13 January 1876, RG0001 Series 1, Box 4, Folder 3. Records of the Board of Trustees, Special Collections Research Center, Gelman Library, The George Washington University, Washington, D.C.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collections consists of typed stenographic notes relating to the activities of the Central Conference. The documents range in date from 1954-2010. The articles include committee meetings, contract negotiations, grievance hearings, change of operations statuses and discharge cases under the National Master Freight Agreement. The Agreement was signed in 1964 between the Teamsters and individual trucking companies. Teamsters General President James R. Hoffa played a large role in the Agreement's passage. The contract established rules and regulations for freight industry employees. It also created uniform wages and working conditions for truck drivers, warehousemen and dockworkers throughout America.
